    id: '71',
    name: 'Leadership Conference',
    slug: 'intl-nursing-leadership-conference',
    type: 'classroom',
    training_loc: '127',
    category: 'Leadership',
    image: 'conferenceghana.jpg',
    initial_cost: '54225',
    cost: '36000',
    description:
      '<p>Themed "Expanded Scope of Discourse of Health and Healthcare Promotion in the Context of the Sustainable Development Goals&rdquo; The conference will be held from Wednesday, April 10th&nbsp; &ndash;&nbsp; Friday, April 12th, 2019 at the University of Ghana, Accra.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Target Audience for the Pre-conference and Main Leadership conference</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pre &ndash;Conference Workshop (8th -9th April, 2019)</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Target audience:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registrars of Nursing and Midwifery Councils</li>\r\n<li>Board members of Nursing Councils</li>\r\n<li>Executives of Professional Associations</li>\r\n<li>Heads of Departments/Faculty/Colleges/Schools of Nursing and Midwifery</li>\r\n<li>Directors of Nursing Services at Public and Private Institutions</li>\r\n<li>Proprietors of Health Institutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Objectives</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To articulate progress made in development of countries&rsquo; plans of action for the achievement of SDGs</li>\r\n<li>To complete and ratify the Working Documents (constitutions, policies, administrative structure, plan of action, monitoring and evaluation plan, strategies for funding) on Implementing Nursing Agenda for the Achievement of Sustainable Development Goals in Africa.</li>\r\n<li>To explore alternative models of nursing interventions that can drive expanded scope of coverage of health promotion and comprehensive healthcare access</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Main Leadership Conference: 10th&nbsp;&ndash; 12th&nbsp;April, 2019</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Theme:</strong>&nbsp;Expanded Scope of Discourse of Healthcare and Healthcare Promotion in the context of Achievement of the Sustainable development Goals.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Target Audience</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nursing and Midwifery Leaders Across All Levels of Professional Development and Practice</li>\r\n<li>Registered Nurses and Midwives</li>\r\n<li>Consumers of Health</li>\r\n<li>Healthcare Service Organizations (Government and Non-Governmental)</li>\r\n<li>Other Healthcare Professionals (in Public and Private Practice)</li>\r\n<li>Students</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slogan:</strong>&nbsp;All for health, health for all!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goal:</strong>&nbsp;Advancing health promotion across the life cycle and driving healthcare systems and industry that work for all in Africa</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sub &ndash; Objectives</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To document demands and practices for health promotion, enhanced healthcare provision and enhanced access for the achievement of Sustainable Development Goals</li>\r\n<li>To share experiences among stakeholders on practices enhancing health promotion and healthcare access towards the achievement of Sustainable Development Goals<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Framework for discussions</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>From demand to Idea</li>\r\n<li>From Idea to Innovation</li>\r\n<li>From Innovation to practice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Focus:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Capacity building for critical analysis and discourses for enhanced health promotion practices, enhanced healthcare provision and enhanced healthcare access for achievement of Sustainable development Goals.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Methods:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working Sessions Focus on Exploring practices for health promotion practices, moderators of social determinants of health and the implications for individual, organizational and institutional, government, and non-governmental interventions for quality access to health and healthcare.</li>\r\n<li>Generating innovative nursing interventions to enhance quality access to health and healthcare services in Africa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Updates:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We propose to keep generating updates on new knowledge, new technology and best practice for health promotion and quality healthcare provision/access for population health.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delegate fees</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pre-Conference &amp; Conference = 200 USD (The leaders attending the Pre-conference are expected to join the conference)</li>\r\n<li>Conference fee = 150 USD (100 USD for early registration).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>MORE INFORMATION</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>DELEGATE FEE</strong> : 100 USD or N36,000 or 500GH (covers conference materials, tea break and lunch)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>ACCOMMODATION</strong> : <br />There are 4 Categories of Accommodation. <br />1. 35 USD per night - 30 rooms available <br />2. 40 USD per night - 40 rooms available<br />3. 50 USD per night : 50 rooms available<br />4. 60 USD per night : 100 rooms available<br />All rooms can take a maximum of 2 persons.</p>\r\n<p>The organizing committee are still making arrangements for cheaper rooms.</p>\r\n<p>There are also hotels around Legon; you can book around the conference location but ensure to budget extra 10 USD for shuttle through the event.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TRANSPORTATION</strong> :<br />East Africa : - It is advisable to use Kenyan airways or Rwanda air. Most delegates have booked theirs, so, there are no provisions for group arrangements.</p>\r\n<p>Southern Africa : Interested participants from South Africa to kindly mail to hello@healhrak.com to be linked to your conference travel agent.</p>\r\n<p>West Africa : Benin Republic and Togo are close to Ghana. Other countries within the region have small delegation and would sort themselves out.</p>\r\n<p>Nigeria : Due to population, there are 2 options for transportation available to participants from Nigeria.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>FLIGHT</strong>: Return flight tickets from Lagos to Accra : 300 USD; negotiations are on for lower flight fares. You can currently book return ticket from Jumia at N83,000.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>ROAD</strong>:<br />a) Bus fare N40,000 - Return ticket for participants using their International passports <br />b) Bus fare N45,000 - Return ticket for participants using any other ID card</p>\r\n<p>Breakfast and dinner: Budget 1 - 2 USD for a regular meal at a decent and 3 - 5 USD per meal in a hotel.</p>\r\n<p>Shuttle from the designated hotels to the conference venue will be planned by the organizers.</p>\r\n<p>Participants lodging outside the accommodation arranged by the organizers will be responsible for their transportation but assistance will be available for those who would need directions on their way around.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ps</strong>: Fees will be calculated based on prevailing dollar rate.</p>\r\n<p>Organized by LeadNurse Africa International Foundation in collaboration with the School of Nursing and Midwifery, University of Ghana</p>',
