    description:
      '<p>Take a CPR (cardiopulmonary resuscitation) class and get trained to use an automated external defibrillator, or AED. It could mean the difference between life and death.</p>\r\n<p>The first step in saving a life is being able to recognize an emergency. Anyone who is unresponsive should receive emergency care, and By standers should be trained to identify the warning signs of a heart attack, mobilize for an ambulance and start a CPR.</p>\r\n<p>Public places, including hotels, bars, shopping malls, airports, and sporting venues now have defibrillators on hand in case of emergency and employees should be trained on AED and CPR.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong>: 4 hours</p>',
