    id: '132',
    name: 'Permit To Work',
    slug: 'permit-to-work',
    type: 'classroom',
    training_loc: '2',
    category: 'Workplace Safety Course\r\n',
    image: 'permit.jpg',
    initial_cost: '100000',
    cost: '100000',
    description:
      '<p>In a situation where one must undertake hazardous work as part of their job role, a permit to work is required in order to confirm that the environment is fit for work and correct safety measures have been taken. This training course is ideal for those in a position where they must use permit to work systems and ensures that delegates learn why permits to work are necessary, and how to issue, manage, or terminate them. This course will provide participants with the understanding of the purposes of permit to work systems in particular for high risk activities.&nbsp;It ensures that all components of a safe system of work are established before high risk work commences, thereby controlling and reducing risk to individuals and the organisation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Target Audience</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Site managers</li>\r\n<li>Project managers</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance managers</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance personnel</li>\r\n<li>Contract managers</li>\r\n<li>Operational staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The course is aimed at</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Those responsible for implementing permit to work systems</li>\r\n<li>New employees selected by the organisation for issuing and signing off permits to work</li>\r\n<li>Existing personnel in the organisation who issue and sign off permits that require formal training</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What you get</strong></p>\r\n<p>Training manuals</p>\r\n<p>Tea and lunch break</p>\r\n<p>Certification</p>',
