    description:
      '<p>Oil Spill Cleanup covers Oil Spill Response and Control Programs in the Oil &amp; Gas Sector. It is an intense classroom-only course that teaches a system of pre-spill readiness, spill response drills; Incident Command System (ICS); and post-spill reaction planning, strategy, and tactics.</p>\r\n<p>The course covers a technical aspects-overview of oil spill response equipment; the behavior of oil in the marine environment; and spill trajectory and tracking modeling. The course is designed to teach oil-spill crisis communications considerations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Target Audience</strong></p>\r\n<p>The course is designed for Managers who need to assess the readiness of their organization for an Oil Spill Response; Members of the Oil Spill Emergency Response Teams (either as oil-contact field staff or office-based support staff).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What you get</strong></p>\r\n<p>Training manuals</p>\r\n<p>Tea and lunch break</p>\r\n<p>Practicals</p>\r\n<p>Certification</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',
