    image: 'bosietop.jpg',
    initial_cost: '300000',
    cost: '275625',
    description:
      '<p>Basic Offshore Safety Induction and Emergency Training&nbsp;is essential for personnel who are new to the offshore oil and gas industry that require this safety and emergency response training and assessment to work offshore in a cold or tropical water environment.</p>\r\n<p><br />This training provides students with a basic understanding and awareness of the hazards encountered during travel to offshore installations and the emergency procedures to be followed in the event of an offshore incident. Certification is valid for four years from the date of issue.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Course content</strong></p>\r\n<p>Basic Offshore Safety Induction &amp; Emergency Training (BOSIET), which is based on four modules:<br />- Safety induction, <br />- Sea survival (including first aid), <br />- Fire fighting and self-rescue, and <br />- Helicopter safety and escape including HUET (helicopter underwater escape training) with Emergency breathing system (EBS)</p>\r\n<p><br />Escape Chute Training - introduces both theoretical knowledge and practical exercises in the safe use of escape chutes increasingly used on offshore installations and vessels. Certification is valid for four years from the date of issue.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delivery method</strong><br />This training is delivered through classroom presentations, activities and discussions, as well as practicals in a simulated workplace environment using specialized equipment.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Expected outcome</strong><br />At the end of the training, participants should be skilled and knowledgeable in the following:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safety induction</strong><br />Helicopter safety and escape , which includes ;prepare for flight, board the helicopter, prepare for helicopter ditching, undertake evacuation from the helicopter<br />Facilitate recovery process<br />Control hazards<br />Sea survival<br />Firefighting and self rescue</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Offshore Safety Induction Emergency Training runs twice a week day (Monday to Wednesday and Wednesday to Friday)</li>\r\n<li>Participants must be medically fit</li>\r\n<li>Participants are required to come with their swim wear and towel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Course fee include tea break, lunch, training materials and photo ID card pass</p>',
